main event: Two objects were observed at Condon AFS, Oregon on March 21, 1966, believed to be the ECHO II satellite, moving at high speed.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1.5 minutes., The objects were described as being the size of a pinhead., The objects were moving at excessive speed at a 35-degree angle., No photographs were taken during the sighting., The area of sighting was clear with no obstructions.
sighted object: two unidentified objects, possibly ECHO II satellite
witness description: Military personnel observing from the ground.
